  "prompt": "How much do astrophysicists make at NASA?",
  "response": "Salaries for astrophysicists at NASA can vary widely depending on factors such as education level, experience, specific job role, location, and other considerations. However, on average, a NASA astrophysicist may earn somewhere between $80,000 to $150,000 annually. More senior positions or those with substantial experience can command higher salaries, sometimes over $150,000 per year. It's important to note that these figures are estimations and can vary. Official and updated salary ranges can typically be found through NASA's career pages or government job listings.",
